-- Egypt Brotherhood Officials Charged With Incitement to Violence
-- B y   S a l m a   E l   W a r d a n y
-- 2012-08-14T14:10:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-14/egypt-brotherhood-officials-charged-with-incitement-to-violence.html
Egypt ’s public prosecutor referred
four senior members of the Muslim Brotherhood to State Security
Prosecution on charges of incitement to attack protesters in
front of the presidential palace in Cairo last month.  The defendants include Mohamed Badea, the Brotherhood’s
supreme guide, millionaire businessman Khairat el-Shater, the
deputy head of the Brotherhood’s Freedom and Justice party,
Essam el-Erian, and the party’s Secretary General Mohamed Saad
al-Katatny, the state-run Ahram Gate website reported today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Salma El Wardany in Cairo at 
 selwardany@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Louis Meixler at 
 lmeixler@bloomberg.net  